Erich Honecker , former head of East Germany , died on 29 May 1994 in Santiago Chile .
He had been living there since his release from prison in 1993 .
Honecker and his regime were toppled in October 1989 , by pro-democracy demonstrators , leading to the eventual unification of East and West Germany .
He , along with several members of his Politburo , were arrested and charges with treason , corruption , and abuse of power .
Honecker was also charged with manslaughter , stemming from his orders , which resulted in the deaths of East Germans attempting to flee to the West .
Honecker ruled East Germany for 18 years by using extreme repression .
